            <fr:title text="Modules over PIDs are torsion-free iff isomorphic to a submodule of a free module">Modules over PIDs are torsion-free iff isomorphic to a submodule of a free module</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/ra-001M/" title="Principal Ideal Domain" uri="http://localhost:8000/ra-001M/" display-uri="ra-001M" type="local">Principal Ideal Domain</fr:link>, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/ra-004A/" title="Finitely-Generated Submodule" uri="http://localhost:8000/ra-004A/" display-uri="ra-004A" type="local">finitely-generated</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>-module. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/ra-003P/" title="Torsion-Free Module" uri="http://localhost:8000/ra-003P/" display-uri="ra-003P" type="local">torsion-free</fr:link> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> is isomorphic to a submodule of a free module.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>19</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longleftarrow )]]></fr:tex> Any submodule of a free module over an integral domain is torsion-free.</html:p>
<html:p><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longrightarrow )]]></fr:tex> Assume <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is torsion-free. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be the set of all linearly-independent subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>. We can check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is nonempty (since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> being torsion-free and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> being an integral domain that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{m\}]]></fr:tex> is linearly independent for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\in  M]]></fr:tex> nonzero <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\neq 0]]></fr:tex>) and all ascending chains in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> admit an upper bound. Then by <fr:link href="/zorn's-lemma/" title="Zorn's lemma" uri="http://localhost:8000/zorn's-lemma/" display-uri="zorn's-lemma" type="local">Zorn's lemma</fr:link> there exists a maximal element in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>. That is to say, there exists a maximal free submodule <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
<html:p>We claim that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M/F]]></fr:tex> is torsion. If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m+F\in  M]]></fr:tex> is not torsion, then the submodule <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Rm+F]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is free and it properly contains <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is assumed to be torsion free, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Rm]]></fr:tex> is free and thus it suffices to check <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Rm\cap  F=(0)]]></fr:tex>. But <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[rm\in  F]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r(m+F)=0]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is finitely-generated then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M/F]]></fr:tex> is finitely-generated and torsion. Then there exists some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  R]]></fr:tex> nonzero <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\neq 0]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a(M/F)=0]]></fr:tex>. Equivalently <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[aM\subseteq  F]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is torsion-free, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is isomorphic to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[aM]]></fr:tex>.</html:p><html:span class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
